{"title_page": "Giorgos Koutroubis", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Giorgos Koutroubis\n| image         = \u0414\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043c\u043e-\u041f\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0441 (12).jpg\n| image_size    = 250px\n| fullname      = Georgios Koutroubis\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1991|2|10}}\n| birth_place   = [[Athens]], Greece\n| height        = {{convert|1.90|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position      = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre-back]]\n| currentclub   = [[OFI Crete|OFI]]\n| clubnumber    = 5\n| years1 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs1 = [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]               | caps1 = 50 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs2 = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]             | caps2 = 29 | goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2013\u20132018 | clubs3 = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]       | caps3 = 93 | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2018      | clubs4 = [[Royal Standard de Li\u00e8ge|Standard Li\u00e8ge]] | caps4 =  7 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2019      | clubs5 = [[CS Concordia Chiajna|Concordia Chiajna]] | caps5 =  9 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2019\u2013     | clubs6 =[[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]]                      | caps6 =  19 | goals6 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalteam1  = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U19]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate     = {{date|2020-3-1}}\n| ntupdate     = {{date|2013-08-19}}\n}}\n'''Giorgos Koutroubis''' ({{lang-el|\u0393\u03b9\u03ce\u03c1\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2 \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2}}; born 10 February 1991) is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Athens]], \u039aoutroubis started his professional career in the [[Football League]] playing for [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]. On 9 August 2012, with a personal interference from ex [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] president and major shareholder [[Dimitris Melissanidis]], signed a four years' contract with AEK Athens for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Aek/kitrinomayros-o-koytroymphs-me-paremvash-melissanidh.1887526.html|script-title=el:\"\u039a\u03b9\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03bd\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c5\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2\" \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2, \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c0\u03b1\u03c1\u03ad\u03bc\u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u039c\u03b5\u03bb\u03b9\u03c3\u03c3\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7!|language=el|date=9 August 2012|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> After AEK Athens' relegation, Koutroubis due to his club financial problems, asked for his contract to be solved, trying to sign with rivals [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]].\n\n===Panathinaikos===\nKoutroubis could not be officially announced by [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]], because he still had a contract with [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]. On June 26, 2013, he participated in [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] first training session for the [[2013-14 Superleague Greece|2013-14 season]]. On July 2, 2013, he filed an appeal against [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]], in order to get whatever the team owed to him. On the same day, he travelled to the Netherlands and Osterberg, in order to take part in Panathinaikos' summer preparation.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.gr/football/article/521008/prosfygi-stin-aek-o-koytroympis|script-title=el:\u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c6\u03c5\u03b3\u03ae \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u0395\u039a \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|trans-title=Koutroupis appeals to AEK|language=el|date=3 July 2013|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 17 July 2013, it was officially announced that Koutroubis had signed a four-years contract with [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sentragoal.gr/article.asp?catid=39435&subid=2&pubid=129407701|script-title=el:\u0393\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03b1 \u03c7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b9\u03b1 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc!|trans-title=Koutroupis joins Panathinaikos! for three years|language=el|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.naftemporiki.gr/story/676431/panathinaikos-anakoinothike-o-koutroumpis|script-title=el:\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2: \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03ce\u03b8\u03b7\u03ba\u03b5 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|trans-title=Panathinaikos: Koutroupis signed the contract|language=el|date=17 July 2013|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn summer 2016, [[Adanaspor]] are monitoring the case of [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]' 25-year-old central defender Giorgos Koutroubis, whose current contract expires at summer of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prasinanea.gr/podosfairo/o-koutroumpis-sti-lista-tis-antanaspor/|script-title=el:\u039f \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03bb\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03bd\u03c4\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c3\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1|trans-title=Koutroupis is enlisted with Adanaspor|language=el|date=19 July 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 6 October 2016, negotiations started for the extension of his contract. Koutroubis is among the players Panathinaikos wish to tie up at the club as the two parties has begun negotiations over a new deal and the Greens are willing to offer an improved salary to the 25-year-old central defender, whose current contract expires at the end of 2016-17 season, in order to keep him in their squad. Italian manager of Panathinaikos [[Andrea Stramaccioni]] will handle personally the case of Giorgos Koutroubis' contract extension until the summer of 2019. Eventually, on 15 October 2016, the current contract of 25-year-old player that expired at summer of 2017, will be extended until that of 2019, with better financial terms (\u20ac250,000 per year) and a buy-out clause of \u20ac1,6 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novasports.gr/podosfairo/ellada/super-league/article/278942/upografei-neo-sumvolaio-o-koutroubis/#.WAtzGyQxR_E|script-title=el:\u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03ac\u03c6\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03c3\u03c5\u03bc\u03b2\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03b9\u03bf \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|trans-title=Koutroupis signs new contract|language=el|date=21 June 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/superleague/article/254400/symfonise-gia-neo-symvolaio-o-koytroympis|script-title=el:\u03a3\u03c5\u03bc\u03c6\u03ce\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03c3\u03c5\u03bc\u03b2\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03b9\u03bf \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2!|trans-title=Koutroboumis agrees to a new contract!|language=el|date=15 October 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 October 2016, the directors of [[Trabzonspor]] are monitoring the case of [[Panathinaikos]]' defender, despite the fact that the new contract with the Greens expires at summer of 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://panathinaikos24.gr/2016/10/21/maties-trabzonspor-ston-koutroubi/|script-title=el:\u00ab\u039c\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ad\u03c2\u00bb \u03a4\u03c1\u03ac\u03bc\u03c0\u03b6\u03bf\u03bd\u03c3\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae|publisher=[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]|language=el|date=21 October 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 10 September 2017, [[Marinos Ouzounidis]] named the international defender as the new captain of the club for the [[2017-18 Superleague Greece|2017-18 season]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Panathinaikos/o-koytroymphs-neos-arxhgos-ston-panathhnaiko.4839497.html|script-title=el:\u039f \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c1\u03c7\u03b7\u03b3\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc|language=el|date=10 September 2017}}</ref> On 15 December 2017, the administration of [[Panathinaikos]] announced to Koutroubis that he will be released from the financially struggling Greens in January 2018. The 26-year-old international central defender joined the historic Athens club from AEK back in the summer of 2013 and his current contract with experienced manager [[Marinos Ouzounidis]]' team expires in June 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thepressroom.gr/sports/panathenaikos-pheygei-o-koytroympes |script-title=el:\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a6\u03b5\u03cd\u03b3\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|language=el|date=15 December 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/superleague/article/409917/lynetai-symvolaio-toy-koytroympi-me-ton-panathinaiko |script-title=el:\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc!|language=el|date=15 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Standard Li\u00e8ge===\nOn 31 January 2018, Koutroubis signed as a free agent, a six months contract (with an option for an additional year) with Belgian club [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plus.lesoir.be/137260/article/2018-01-31/standard-koutroubis-est-en-route-vanheusden-signe# |title=Standard: Koutroubis est en route, Vanheusden a sign\u00e9 |date=31 January 2018}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/EllinesExoterikou/epishmo-sthn-stantar-lieghs-o-koytroymphs.5056454.html |title=\u0395\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03ac\u03c1 \u039b\u03b9\u03ad\u03b3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 |date=31 January 2018}}</ref> On 11 February 2018, he made his debut with the club as a starter in an anxious 4-3 win against [[Royal Excel Mouscron]].\n\nOn 17 March 2018, he played as [[Standard Liege]] beat [[K.R.C. Genk| Genk]] 1-0 in extra time to win the [[2018 Belgian Cup Final]] and qualify for the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.live.sporza.be/cm/lmc.mobile/m_mc_voetbal/Beker-van-Belgie-1718/MG_BVB_F/1.3162424 |title=Archived copy |access-date=23 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180521203352/http://m.live.sporza.be/cm/lmc.mobile/m_mc_voetbal/Beker-van-Belgie-1718/MG_BVB_F/1.3162424 |archive-date=21 May 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> At the end of the season he mutually solved his contract with the club.\n\n===Concordia Chiajna===\nOn 12 February 2019, Koutroubis signed a 6 month contract with Romanian club [[CS Concordia Chiajna]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.csconcordia.ro/acasa/1529-bun-venit-georgios-koutroumpis.html|title=Bun venit, Georgios Koutroumpis!|trans-title=Welcome, Giorgos Koutroubis!|date=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===OFI===\nOn 30 August 2019, Koutroubis signed a 2-years contract with [[Superleague Greece|Superleague]] club [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Ofi/ofh-koytroymphs-dietias-kai-epishma.5586876.html |title=\u039f\u03a6\u0397: \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b5\u03c4\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b5\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1|date=30 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{As of|2020|3|1}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe*\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other**\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"| [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Football League (Greece)|2010-11]]\n|21||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||21||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Football League (Greece)|2011-12]]\n|29||0||1||0||0||0||0||0||30||0\n|-\n!Total\n!50!!0!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!51!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"| [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Superleague Greece|2012-13]]\n|29||1||1||0||0||0||0||0||30||1\n|-\n!|Total\n!29!!1!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!30!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\" valign=\"center\"| [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Superleague Greece|2013-14]]\n|25||2||6||0||0||0||6||0||37||2\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Superleague Greece|2014-15]]\n|18||0||2||0||6||0||6||0||32||0\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Superleague Greece|2015-16]]\n|18||0||4||0||4||0||6||0||32||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Superleague Greece|2016-17]]\n|22||0||6||0||10||0||6||0||44||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Superleague Greece|2017-18]]\n|10||0||1||0||2||0||0||0||13||0\n|-\n!|Total\n!93!!2!!19!!0!!22!!0!!24!!0!!158!!2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"| [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]]\n|[[2017\u201318 Belgian First Division A|2017-18]]\n|7||0||1||0||0||0||0||0||8||0\n|-\n!|Total\n!7!!0!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!8!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"| [[CS Concordia Chiajna|Concordia Chiajna]]\n|[[2018\u201319 CS Concordia Chiajna season|2018-19]]\n|9||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||9||0\n|-\n!|Total\n!9!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!9!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"| [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Superleague Greece|2019-20]]\n|19||0||3||0||0||0||0||0||22||0\n|-\n!|Total\n!19!!0!!3!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!22!!0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!207!!3!!25!!0!!22!!0!!24!!0!!278!!3\n|-\n|}\n\n<small>(* Includes [[UEFA Europa League]] and [[UEFA Champions League]])</small>\n<small>(** Includes [[Superleague Greece|SuperLeague Playoffs]] )</small>\n\n==Honours==\n;Panathinaikos\n* [[Greek Cup]]: [[2013\u201314 Greek Football Cup|2014]]\n\n;Standard Li\u00e8ge\n* [[Belgian Cup]]: [[2017\u201318 Belgian Cup|2018]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerway|giorgos-koutroumbis/70391}}\n*[http://www.onsports.gr/onstats/?url=/soccer/player/main.php&sport-select=soccer&player-select=806 Onsports.gr Profile]\n\n{{OFI Crete squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Koutroubis, Giorgos}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Athens]]\n[[Category:Greek footballers]]\n[[Category:Greece youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:Football League (Greece) players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:Kallithea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AEK Athens F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Panathinaikos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Standard Li\u00e8ge players]]\n[[Category:CS Concordia Chiajna players]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate sportspeople in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate sportspeople in Romania]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Romania]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Giorgos Koutroubis\n| image         = \u0414\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043c\u043e-\u041f\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0441 (12).jpg\n| image_size    = 250px\n| fullname      = Georgios Koutroubis\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1991|2|10}}\n| birth_place   = [[Athens]], Greece\n| height        = {{convert|1.90|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position      = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre-back]]\n| currentclub   = [[OFI Crete|OFI]]\n| clubnumber    = 5\n| years1 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs1 = [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]               | caps1 = 50 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs2 = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]             | caps2 = 29 | goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2013\u20132018 | clubs3 = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]       | caps3 = 93 | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2018      | clubs4 = [[Royal Standard de Li\u00e8ge|Standard Li\u00e8ge]] | caps4 =  7 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2019      | clubs5 = [[CS Concordia Chiajna|Concordia Chiajna]] | caps5 =  9 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2019\u2013     | clubs6 =[[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]]                      | caps6 =  19 | goals6 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalteam1  = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U19]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate     = {{date|2020-3-1}}\n| ntupdate     = {{date|2013-08-19}}\n}}\n'''Giorgos Koutroubis''' ({{lang-el|\u0393\u03b9\u03ce\u03c1\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2 \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2}}; born 10 February 1991) is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Athens]], \u039aoutroubis started his professional career in the [[Football League]] playing for [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]. On 9 August 2012, with a personal interference from ex [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] president and major shareholder [[Dimitris Melissanidis]], signed a four years' contract with AEK Athens for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Aek/kitrinomayros-o-koytroymphs-me-paremvash-melissanidh.1887526.html|script-title=el:\"\u039a\u03b9\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03bd\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c5\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2\" \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2, \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c0\u03b1\u03c1\u03ad\u03bc\u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u039c\u03b5\u03bb\u03b9\u03c3\u03c3\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7!|language=el|date=9 August 2012|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> After AEK Athens' relegation, Koutroubis due to his club financial problems, asked for his contract to be solved, trying to sign with rivals [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]].\n\n===Panathinaikos===\nKoutroubis could not be officially announced by [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]], because he still had a contract with [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]. On June 26, 2013, he participated in [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] first training session for the [[2013-14 Superleague Greece|2013-14 season]]. On July 2, 2013, he filed an appeal against [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]], in order to get whatever the team owed to him. On the same day, he travelled to the Netherlands and Osterberg, in order to take part in Panathinaikos' summer preparation.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.gr/football/article/521008/prosfygi-stin-aek-o-koytroympis|script-title=el:\u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c6\u03c5\u03b3\u03ae \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u0395\u039a \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|trans-title=Koutroupis appeals to AEK|language=el|date=3 July 2013|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 17 July 2013, it was officially announced that Koutroubis had signed a four-years contract with [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sentragoal.gr/article.asp?catid=39435&subid=2&pubid=129407701|script-title=el:\u0393\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03b1 \u03c7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b9\u03b1 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc!|trans-title=Koutroupis joins Panathinaikos! for three years|language=el|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.naftemporiki.gr/story/676431/panathinaikos-anakoinothike-o-koutroumpis|script-title=el:\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2: \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03ce\u03b8\u03b7\u03ba\u03b5 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|trans-title=Panathinaikos: Koutroupis signed the contract|language=el|date=17 July 2013|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn summer 2016, [[Adanaspor]] are monitoring the case of [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]' 25-year-old central defender Giorgos Koutroubis, whose current contract expires at summer of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prasinanea.gr/podosfairo/o-koutroumpis-sti-lista-tis-antanaspor/|script-title=el:\u039f \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03bb\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03bd\u03c4\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c3\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1|trans-title=Koutroupis is enlisted with Adanaspor|language=el|date=19 July 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 6 October 2016, negotiations started for the extension of his contract. Koutroubis is among the players Panathinaikos wish to tie up at the club as the two parties has begun negotiations over a new deal and the Greens are willing to offer an improved salary to the 25-year-old central defender, whose current contract expires at the end of 2016-17 season, in order to keep him in their squad. Italian manager of Panathinaikos [[Andrea Stramaccioni]] will handle personally the case of Giorgos Koutroubis' contract extension until the summer of 2019. Eventually, on 15 October 2016, the current contract of 25-year-old player that expired at summer of 2017, will be extended until that of 2019, with better financial terms (\u20ac250,000 per year) and a buy-out clause of \u20ac1,6 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.novasports.gr/podosfairo/ellada/super-league/article/278942/upografei-neo-sumvolaio-o-koutroubis/#.WAtzGyQxR_E|script-title=el:\u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03ac\u03c6\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03c3\u03c5\u03bc\u03b2\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03b9\u03bf \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|trans-title=Koutroupis signs new contract|language=el|date=21 June 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/superleague/article/254400/symfonise-gia-neo-symvolaio-o-koytroympis|script-title=el:\u03a3\u03c5\u03bc\u03c6\u03ce\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03c3\u03c5\u03bc\u03b2\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03b9\u03bf \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2!|trans-title=Koutroboumis agrees to a new contract!|language=el|date=15 October 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 October 2016, the directors of [[Trabzonspor]] are monitoring the case of [[Panathinaikos]]' defender, despite the fact that the new contract with the Greens expires at summer of 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://panathinaikos24.gr/2016/10/21/maties-trabzonspor-ston-koutroubi/|script-title=el:\u00ab\u039c\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ad\u03c2\u00bb \u03a4\u03c1\u03ac\u03bc\u03c0\u03b6\u03bf\u03bd\u03c3\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae|publisher=[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]|language=el|date=21 October 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 10 September 2017, [[Marinos Ouzounidis]] named the international defender as the new captain of the club for the [[2017-18 Superleague Greece|2017-18 season]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Panathinaikos/o-koytroymphs-neos-arxhgos-ston-panathhnaiko.4839497.html|script-title=el:\u039f \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c1\u03c7\u03b7\u03b3\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc|language=el|date=10 September 2017}}</ref> On 15 December 2017, the administration of [[Panathinaikos]] announced to Koutroubis that he will be released from the financially struggling Greens in January 2018. The 26-year-old international central defender joined the historic Athens club from AEK back in the summer of 2013 and his current contract with experienced manager [[Marinos Ouzounidis]]' team expires in June 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thepressroom.gr/sports/panathenaikos-pheygei-o-koytroympes |script-title=el:\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a6\u03b5\u03cd\u03b3\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2|language=el|date=15 December 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/superleague/article/409917/lynetai-symvolaio-toy-koytroympi-me-ton-panathinaiko |script-title=el:\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc!|language=el|date=15 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Standard Li\u00e8ge===\nOn 31 January 2018, Koutroubis signed as a free agent, a six months contract (with an option for an additional year) with Belgian club [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plus.lesoir.be/137260/article/2018-01-31/standard-koutroubis-est-en-route-vanheusden-signe# |title=Standard: Koutroubis est en route, Vanheusden a sign\u00e9 |date=31 January 2018}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/EllinesExoterikou/epishmo-sthn-stantar-lieghs-o-koytroymphs.5056454.html |title=\u0395\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03ac\u03c1 \u039b\u03b9\u03ad\u03b3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03bf \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 |date=31 January 2018}}</ref> On 11 February 2018, he made his debut with the club as a starter in an anxious 4-3 win against [[Royal Excel Mouscron]].\n\nOn 17 March 2018, he played as [[Standard Liege]] beat [[K.R.C. Genk| Genk]] 1-0 in extra time to win the [[2018 Belgian Cup Final]] and qualify for the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.live.sporza.be/cm/lmc.mobile/m_mc_voetbal/Beker-van-Belgie-1718/MG_BVB_F/1.3162424 |title=Archived copy |access-date=23 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180521203352/http://m.live.sporza.be/cm/lmc.mobile/m_mc_voetbal/Beker-van-Belgie-1718/MG_BVB_F/1.3162424 |archive-date=21 May 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> At the end of the season he mutually solved his contract with the club.\n\n===Concordia Chiajna===\nOn 12 February 2019, Koutroubis signed a 6 month contract with Romanian club [[CS Concordia Chiajna]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.csconcordia.ro/acasa/1529-bun-venit-georgios-koutroumpis.html|title=Bun venit, Georgios Koutroumpis!|trans-title=Welcome, Giorgos Koutroubis!|date=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===OFI===\nOn 30 August 2019, Koutroubis signed a 2-years contract with [[Superleague Greece|Superleague]] club [[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Ofi/ofh-koytroymphs-dietias-kai-epishma.5586876.html |title=\u039f\u03a6\u0397: \u039a\u03bf\u03c5\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae\u03c2 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b5\u03c4\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b5\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1|date=30 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{As of|2020|3|1}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe*\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other**\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"| [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Football League (Greece)|2010-11]]\n|21||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||21||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Football League (Greece)|2011-12]]\n|29||0||1||0||0||0||0||0||