jas-selfie-song-is-insanely-viral-hear-it-at-your-own-risk-1695339 |title=Dhinchak Pooja's 'Selfie' Song Is Insanely Viral. Hear It at Your Own Risk |work=NDTV.com |access-date=31 July 2017}}</ref> ''Dilon Ka Shooter'' (2017), ''Baapu Dede Thoda Cash'' (2017),<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/entertainment/dhinchak-pooja-new-song-released-baapu-dede-thoda-cash-watch-video-selfie-maine-leli-aaj-swag-wali-topi-meri-daaru/778240/ |title=Dhinchak Pooja releases new song Baapu Dede Thoda Cash; watch&nbsp;video |date=25 July 2017 |work=The Financial Express |access-date=31 July 2017 }}</ref> and ''Aafreen Fathima Bewafa Hai'' (2017),<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://zeenews.india.com/music/dhinchak-poojas-aafreen-fathima-bewafa-hai-is-breaking-the-internet-watch-2051410.html |title=Dhinchak Pooja's Aafreen Fathima Bewafa Hai is breaking the internet\u2014Watch |date=22 October 2017 |work=Zee News |access-date=13 November 2017 }}</ref> received millions of views on YouTube, shortly after their individual releases.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1140099/teenager-indias-taher-shah/ |title=Is this teenager India's Taher Shah? \u2013 The Express Tribune |date=12 July 2016 |work=The Express Tribune |access-date=31 July 2017 }}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> Her songs have been subject to wide-ranging criticism, and have often been described as part of a new trend of producing cringe-worthy videos to gain web-fame. On 11 June 2017, in response to an individual complaint, YouTube deleted all the song-videos on grounds of privacy violation. The videos, though have been re-uploaded by other users and continue to be available.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/youtuber-dhinchak-poojas-videos-taken-off-her-channel/articleshow/59550924.cms |title=Youtuber Dhinchak Pooja's videos taken off her channel |work=The Times of India |access-date=31 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-40578266 |title=Dhinchak Pooja: What happened to India YouTube 'star' videos? |date=12 July 2017 |publisher=BBC News |access-date=31 July 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.india.com/buzz/dhinchak-pooja-song-videos-deleted-but-you-can-still-watch-dilon-ka-shooter-selfie-maine-leli-aaj-daaru-daaru-and-swag-wali-topi-here-2313967/ |title=Dhinchak Pooja Song Videos Deleted But You Can Still Watch Dilon Ka Shooter, Selfie Maine Leli Aaj, Daaru Daaru and Swag Wali Topi HERE! |last=Mishra |first=Rashmi |date=12 July 2017 |work=India.com |access-date=31 July 2017 }}</ref> Pooja released a new video after a year in 2019 titled ''Naach ke Pagal'' (2019)<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/trending/trending-in-india/dhinchak-pooja-is-back-with-a-new-song-and-everyone-is-wondering-why-its-viral-5860610/ |title=Dhinchak Pooja is back with a new single, and so are the memes; watch&nbsp;video |date=29 July 2019 |work=The indian express |access-date=29 July 2019 }}</ref>, which she has since deleted from her youtube channel.\n\n== Other activities ==\nShe featured on [[BBC Radio]]'s [[Asian Network]], in an episode titled: \"Dhinchak Pooja and Nakash Aziz\" and in a programme by [[Tommy Sandhu]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p057csfz |title=Dhinchak Pooja and Nakash Aziz, Tommy Sandhu's Best Bits&nbsp;\u2014 BBC Asian Network |publisher=BBC |access-date=1 August 2017}}</ref> Jain was chosen as a participant in ''[[Bigg Boss 11]]'', through a wild card<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tv/bigg-boss-11-wildcard-entrant-dhinchak-pooja-all-you-need-to-know-about-the-online-sensation/articleshow/61188769.cms |title=Bigg Boss 11 wildcard entrant Dhinchak Pooja: All you need to know about the online sensation&nbsp;\u2014 Mumbai Mirror \u2013 |work=Mumbai Mirror |access-date=13 November 2017}}</ref> she was evicted on 5 November 2017.\n\n== Television ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year